284
00:18:05,060 --> 00:18:06,460
Don't you know him?

285
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:09,330
- What's Kkeobeong?
- That's you.

286
00:18:09,460 --> 00:18:10,500
You look like him.

287
00:18:14,770 --> 00:18:17,640
Hold it up. This is the injured arm.

288
00:18:18,340 --> 00:18:19,770
Gosh.

289
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:21,980
I have to make dinner.

290
00:18:22,210 --> 00:18:24,180
I did well on my midterms.

291
00:18:24,510 --> 00:18:26,180
If I do well on the practical exam,

292
00:18:26,310 --> 00:18:28,220
I might bring my mark up.

293
00:18:28,220 --> 00:18:31,690
That's why I'm letting
you do this to my head.

294
00:18:32,590 --> 00:18:35,890
But looking at you, this is not your thing.

295
00:18:36,460 --> 00:18:40,260
You're bad with your hands
just like your dad.

296
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:42,960
- Don't you agree?
- She just needs practice.

297
00:18:43,470 --> 00:18:45,830
Come and grab this. Is anyone home?

298
00:18:45,870 --> 00:18:47,870
Yes. Coming!

299
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,840
Are you home?

300
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:53,070
The manager kept on insisting I take this.

301
00:18:58,610 --> 00:19:00,450
Did you get hurt? How?

302
00:19:01,180 --> 00:19:03,790
- It's not...
- Why won't you...

303
00:19:03,850 --> 00:19:05,890
be careful?

304
00:19:06,020 --> 00:19:08,660
Don't get hurt. Don't take it off.

305
00:19:18,070 --> 00:19:21,240
What's going on? What's with the bandages?

306
00:19:21,740 --> 00:19:23,370
It's Jung Hee's homework.

307
00:19:24,710 --> 00:19:25,710
Homework?

308
00:19:28,780 --> 00:19:30,710
Gosh, what a bother.

309
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:37,550
What's with the fuss? It's not like him.

310
00:19:37,890 --> 00:19:41,220
He acted like Bong Soo got hurt.

311
00:20:11,190 --> 00:20:13,350
Are you back?

312
00:20:13,660 --> 00:20:17,090
It feels like you're always wiping...

313
00:20:17,090 --> 00:20:19,630
this disgusting chamber pot.

314
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:21,360
Gosh.

315
00:20:27,070 --> 00:20:29,100
By the way,

316
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:31,210
you said that...

317
00:20:31,370 --> 00:20:33,880
you got separated with your husband?

318
00:20:34,810 --> 00:20:36,610
It's not really a separation.

319
00:20:37,150 --> 00:20:38,910
I was thrown out.

320
00:20:38,910 --> 00:20:41,150
Did he find a new woman?

321
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:43,050
Yes.

322
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:47,220
What an evil man. He deserves to die.

323
00:20:47,690 --> 00:20:49,620
How can he leave such a beautiful wife?

324
00:20:57,900 --> 00:21:00,700
You should find yourself a partner.

325
00:21:01,940 --> 00:21:03,810
How can you keep living like this?

326
00:21:07,580 --> 00:21:10,480
Right. We should be receiving...

327
00:21:10,810 --> 00:21:12,710
the fabric at the factory today.

328
00:21:13,450 --> 00:21:14,750
I'll get going.

329
00:21:28,230 --> 00:21:29,330
Now,

330
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:31,500
we'll pick partners to perform...

331
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:33,540
our bandaging practical exam.

332
00:21:39,070 --> 00:21:40,540
Park Gwi Ja...

333
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:43,750
and Kim Uhn Joo.

334
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:47,250
Kim Ki Ryuh...

335
00:21:49,720 --> 00:21:51,090
and Shim Ae Sook.

336
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:55,560
Lee Jung Hee...

337
00:21:57,460 --> 00:21:58,830
You're lucky, Jung Hee.

338
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:01,360
Park Hae Joo.

339
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,570
I'm jealous.

340
00:22:03,930 --> 00:22:05,470
Ahn Jae Yeon...

341
00:22:06,130 --> 00:22:07,270
and Kim Hong Joo.

342
00:22:07,870 --> 00:22:10,040
- Ki Ryuh.
- Stay still.

343
00:22:10,040 --> 00:22:11,340
How do I use this?

344
00:22:11,340 --> 00:22:13,580
- You have to do this.
- I know.

345
00:22:13,580 --> 00:22:14,640
What are you doing?

346
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:17,350
Do you want to go practice at home?

347
00:22:17,950 --> 00:22:19,310
No way.

348
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:21,980
You want to go to your place...

349
00:22:22,720 --> 00:22:24,050
to practice?

350
00:22:25,890 --> 00:22:29,290
My dad is ill,

351
00:22:29,620 --> 00:22:30,830
so I'm worried.

352
00:22:35,330 --> 00:22:37,900
We can practice here if you don't want to.

353
00:22:40,570 --> 00:22:43,810
It's okay. Let's go to your place.

354
00:22:52,450 --> 00:22:53,550
- Done.
- Guys.

355
00:22:54,150 --> 00:22:56,520
Here, have some of this.

356
00:22:56,520 --> 00:22:57,850
Dad, that's heavy.

357
00:22:57,850 --> 00:22:59,320
- No, no.
- I was going to bring it.

358
00:22:59,320 --> 00:23:01,890
It's okay, I'm fine now.

359
00:23:02,220 --> 00:23:04,790
Jung Hee, do you like tteokbokki?

360
00:23:04,790 --> 00:23:06,660
I make a mean tteokbokki.

361
00:23:06,660 --> 00:23:07,800
Do you want some?

362
00:23:08,760 --> 00:23:10,530
Yes, please make it for us.

363
00:23:10,670 --> 00:23:12,900
His tteokbokki is the best.

364
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:15,800
Great. Let me make some.

365
00:23:16,070 --> 00:23:17,170
Hae Joo.

366
00:23:17,170 --> 00:23:20,070
-Yes?
- Play some music.

367
00:23:20,070 --> 00:23:21,740
Oh, right.

368
00:23:24,380 --> 00:23:25,980
I'll take requests.

369
00:23:25,980 --> 00:23:27,920
Okay, then...

370
00:23:28,450 --> 00:23:30,220
I want Hyun Kyung and
Young Ae's "I Miss You".

371
00:23:30,220 --> 00:23:32,120
That's a good one.

372
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:34,090
I want to listen to Hye Eun Yi.

373
00:23:34,960 --> 00:23:36,120
What about you, Jung Hee?

374
00:23:37,690 --> 00:23:38,790
I'm not sure.

375
00:23:39,230 --> 00:23:41,200
Hae Joo, play "Hey Jude" too.

376
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,960
Okay, sure.

377
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:50,140
It was shocking.

378
00:23:50,140 --> 00:23:52,440
- Dad.
- What?

379
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:55,380
Unlike my dad who calls me names...

380
00:23:55,610 --> 00:23:57,980
and practices authority over us,

381
00:23:59,180 --> 00:24:00,380
Hae Joo's dad...

382
00:24:00,980 --> 00:24:03,250
was nice like a friend.

383
00:24:04,390 --> 00:24:07,520
To me, it was shocking.

384
00:24:10,060 --> 00:24:11,630
Here, try it.

385
00:24:24,670 --> 00:24:25,670
How is it?

386
00:24:27,380 --> 00:24:28,610
It's delicious.

387
00:24:31,510 --> 00:24:33,850
I was so nervous. Wait.

388
00:24:34,020 --> 00:24:35,280
I'll bring you water.

389
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:36,350
Okay.

390
00:24:39,090 --> 00:24:40,190
My dad...

391
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:42,460
must be in a good mood.

392
00:24:53,170 --> 00:24:55,200
Thank you, Jung Hee.

393
00:24:55,870 --> 00:24:57,310
For what?

394
00:24:57,870 --> 00:24:59,310
For coming over.

395
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:03,910
It's been a long time...

396
00:25:03,910 --> 00:25:05,350
since I've seen him smile.

397
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:08,350
Come over often.

398
00:25:08,980 --> 00:25:10,050
Will you?

399
00:25:11,090 --> 00:25:12,090
Come on.

400
00:25:13,660 --> 00:25:14,660
Okay.

401
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:23,870
Dad!

402
00:25:24,270 --> 00:25:26,070
- Are you okay?
- I'm okay.

403
00:25:26,070 --> 00:25:28,070
- I'm fine.
- Dad!

404
00:25:28,240 --> 00:25:30,570
No! What do I do? Dad!

405
00:25:30,570 --> 00:25:32,470
Are you okay? What do I do?

406
00:25:32,470 --> 00:25:33,610
Dad!

407
00:25:34,280 --> 00:25:35,340
Dad!

408
00:25:36,410 --> 00:25:38,010
Dad!

409
00:25:45,390 --> 00:25:46,820
Yes, Jung Hee.

410
00:25:48,420 --> 00:25:49,420
Hae Joo...

411
00:25:50,290 --> 00:25:51,760
Hae Joo's dad...

412
00:25:58,200 --> 00:26:00,570
Dad. Dad...

413
00:26:04,070 --> 00:26:05,570
- Be careful.
- Okay.

414
00:26:10,780 --> 00:26:12,380
Be careful. Good.

415
00:26:13,820 --> 00:26:15,650
Hae Joo, I'll be right behind you.

416
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,000
Jung Hee.

417
00:26:31,500 --> 00:26:32,570
Jung Hee!

418
00:26:35,040 --> 00:26:36,770
- What happened?
- Dong Moon,

419
00:26:36,970 --> 00:26:38,470
Hae Joo's dad...

420
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:47,320
You must be startled.

421
00:26:47,350 --> 00:26:48,420
It's okay.

422
00:26:49,720 --> 00:26:51,020
He'll be fine.

423
00:26:54,860 --> 00:26:57,290
- What did you say?
- We performed first aid,

424
00:26:57,290 --> 00:26:59,260
but our director is in Seoul right now.

425
00:26:59,260 --> 00:27:01,300
He can't get treatment right away.

426
00:27:01,300 --> 00:27:04,370
Then please send him to another hospital.

427
00:27:04,900 --> 00:27:07,940
I'm scared if something very serious...

428
00:27:07,940 --> 00:27:09,040
has happened to him.

429
00:27:09,040 --> 00:27:11,240
That's not something I can decide.

430
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:13,540
Someone's life is on the line.

431
00:27:13,540 --> 00:27:15,510
You can't decide?

432
00:27:16,780 --> 00:27:19,450
Are you joking me? If there is no doctor,

433
00:27:19,450 --> 00:27:20,950
then find us a new hospital!

434
00:27:20,950 --> 00:27:23,080
Who are you yelling at?

435
00:27:23,080 --> 00:27:24,090
It's not like that...

436
00:27:24,090 --> 00:27:25,990
The patient coughed up blood and fainted.

437
00:27:25,990 --> 00:27:27,790
How can you say that?

438
00:27:27,790 --> 00:27:29,060
Jung Hee.

439
00:27:29,590 --> 00:27:32,660
Ma'am, please send him to another hospital.

440
00:27:34,430 --> 00:27:35,700
I'll look at him.

441
00:27:35,700 --> 00:27:37,730
What brings you here, sir?

442
00:27:37,730 --> 00:27:39,200
- Is this the room?
- Yes.

443
00:27:41,700 --> 00:27:42,770
I brought him.

444
00:27:42,770 --> 00:27:44,640
How did you know?

445
00:27:44,640 --> 00:27:46,470
I called Jin.

446
00:27:48,880 --> 00:27:50,580
He's my uncle.

447
00:27:50,950 --> 00:27:52,680
He works at a university hospital.

448
00:27:52,750 --> 00:27:54,580
He talked to the director of this hospital,

449
00:27:54,580 --> 00:27:55,880
so he'll take good care of your dad.

450
00:27:57,290 --> 00:27:58,620
Thank you.

451
00:27:59,690 --> 00:28:02,020
Thank you so much, Jin.

452
00:28:23,040 --> 00:28:25,510
It's tuberculosis? Is it serious?

453
00:28:25,510 --> 00:28:27,650
We don't have to worry for now.

454
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:39,030
Really? What do we do?

455
00:28:39,630 --> 00:28:41,260
Is he okay now?

456
00:28:41,330 --> 00:28:42,460
Yes.

457
00:28:43,500 --> 00:28:46,700
That's why I have to stay here for tonight.

458
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:48,440
Hae Joo doesn't have a mom,

459
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:49,900
so I feel bad for her.

460
00:28:50,610 --> 00:28:51,910
Tell Mom...

461
00:28:51,910 --> 00:28:54,540
I'm staying at Eun Ja's
to practice for the exam.

462
00:28:55,010 --> 00:28:56,080
Hey.

463
00:28:57,080 --> 00:28:58,180
Hello?

464
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:03,220
Okay, I got it.

465
00:29:03,220 --> 00:29:05,320
Call me if something happens.

466
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:06,720
Okay, be careful.

467
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:07,860
Okay.

468
00:29:09,590 --> 00:29:11,090
Ma'am...

469
00:29:13,260 --> 00:29:15,830
Jung Hee is definitely your daughter.

470
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:19,500
She tells you whenever something happens.

471
00:29:20,770 --> 00:29:23,100
That's not true.

472
00:29:30,410 --> 00:29:31,580
Take some food...

473
00:29:31,580 --> 00:29:34,720
to the hospital tomorrow for Jung Hee.

474
00:29:36,050 --> 00:29:37,490
Okay.

475
00:29:48,500 --> 00:29:50,300
That girl...

476
00:29:50,900 --> 00:29:54,070
Why is she scared of telling me the truth?

477
00:29:57,090 --> 00:30:00,330
[VIU Ver] E06 Girls' Generation 1979
"Dangerous Instincts" -= Ruo Xi =-

478
00:30:08,580 --> 00:30:11,750
Do you really not have to go home?

479
00:30:11,950 --> 00:30:13,890
My mom gave me permission.

480
00:30:15,190 --> 00:30:17,790
Your parents don't complain...

481
00:30:17,890 --> 00:30:19,360
about being with me?

482
00:30:19,990 --> 00:30:21,030
What?

483
00:30:22,260 --> 00:30:23,470
I know...

484
00:30:24,300 --> 00:30:27,040
that the adults don't like my family.

485
00:30:29,270 --> 00:30:30,810
What do you mean?

486
00:30:31,340 --> 00:30:33,140
Why would they not?

487
00:30:34,240 --> 00:30:36,910
I'm so envious of you.

488
00:30:38,210 --> 00:30:41,680
I grew up with a father
who constantly says...

489
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:45,720
"a girl" this, "a girl" that.

490
00:30:47,660 --> 00:30:50,660
I've never seen a father who's so nice...

491
00:30:50,830 --> 00:30:52,190
to his daughter.

492
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:57,930
You have no idea how much I envy you.

493
00:31:00,640 --> 00:31:02,540
Thank you, Jung Hee.

494
00:31:05,970 --> 00:31:07,580
Shouldn't...

495
00:31:08,340 --> 00:31:10,680
Dong Moon go home?

496
00:31:10,910 --> 00:31:12,010
It's fine.

497
00:31:14,150 --> 00:31:15,980
My family doesn't care about me.

498
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:17,890
Liar.

499
00:31:22,020 --> 00:31:23,530
Your dad's awake.

500
00:32:05,730 --> 00:32:06,800
Hi.

501
00:32:09,240 --> 00:32:11,310
My dad came home.

502
00:32:15,410 --> 00:32:16,750
Thank you.

503
00:32:18,080 --> 00:32:19,410
I didn't do anything.

504
00:32:19,750 --> 00:32:20,920
Mister.

505
00:32:21,250 --> 00:32:23,520
I know you stayed at the hospital...

506
00:32:24,320 --> 00:32:25,420
until morning.

507
00:32:29,560 --> 00:32:32,560
It made me feel safe.

508
00:32:34,830 --> 00:32:36,230
I wasn't afraid.

509
00:32:41,370 --> 00:32:43,070
Goodness.

510
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:47,980
Don't you have a delivery to make?

511
00:32:47,980 --> 00:32:50,350
- I'm going.
- Hurry up.

512
00:32:54,720 --> 00:32:56,480
- I'll be right back.
- Okay.

513
00:33:03,560 --> 00:33:05,690
Do you mean it?

514
00:33:06,460 --> 00:33:07,600
Yes.

515
00:33:08,530 --> 00:33:10,730
Your father processed it.

516
00:33:14,170 --> 00:33:17,970
He also said if you see
that girl Hae Joo again,

517
00:33:18,540 --> 00:33:20,780
it'll be bad for her father.

518
00:33:29,520 --> 00:33:30,750
Where are you going?

519
00:33:35,620 --> 00:33:36,690
Jin.

520
00:33:59,810 --> 00:34:02,350
He also said if you see
that girl Hae Joo again,

521
00:34:02,950 --> 00:34:05,150
it'll be bad for her father.

522
00:34:11,060 --> 00:34:12,190
Jin.

523
00:34:18,470 --> 00:34:19,500
Jung Hee.

524
00:34:21,240 --> 00:34:24,010
Are you here to see Hae Joo?

525
00:34:24,810 --> 00:34:25,910
What?

526
00:34:25,910 --> 00:34:27,810
I'll get her.

527
00:34:36,890 --> 00:34:38,850
- Jung Hee.
- Yes?

528
00:34:39,520 --> 00:34:40,660
Do you want...

529
00:34:41,890 --> 00:34:43,090
to watch a movie?

530
00:34:47,660 --> 00:34:48,860
Can you...

531
00:34:50,430 --> 00:34:52,870
just stay with me?

532
00:34:56,300 --> 00:35:00,110
I'm sure Jin came to see Hae Joo.

533
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:04,010
I'm sure I'm an excuse.

534
00:35:05,150 --> 00:35:06,310
But...

535
00:35:12,990 --> 00:35:14,020
Sorry.

536
00:35:16,830 --> 00:35:17,960
I'll go.

537
00:35:26,270 --> 00:35:29,600
I know that, but I couldn't refuse...

538
00:35:30,310 --> 00:35:34,040
because he looked so sad.

539
00:35:39,310 --> 00:35:40,520
Why are you so late?

540
00:35:40,950 --> 00:35:44,620
Sorry. Can you smell my uniform for me?

541
00:35:48,820 --> 00:35:49,890
Where's Jung Hee?

542
00:35:50,490 --> 00:35:51,830
I thought she was back.

543
00:35:52,230 --> 00:35:53,330
Jung Hee?

544
00:35:53,660 --> 00:35:57,170
She was all excited about going on a date.

545
00:35:58,500 --> 00:36:00,000
A date?

546
00:36:00,140 --> 00:36:01,240
That's right.

547
00:36:02,170 --> 00:36:04,410
With Jin?

548
00:36:04,470 --> 00:36:05,510
That's right.

549
00:36:05,510 --> 00:36:09,040
They took the bus and went far, far away.

550
00:36:09,040 --> 00:36:10,750
They're very meticulous.

551
00:36:10,780 --> 00:36:11,910
Meticulous?

552
00:36:15,080 --> 00:36:18,020
Don't you worry. You have me.

553
00:36:24,990 --> 00:36:28,100
I've always dreamed of this moment.

554
00:36:29,230 --> 00:36:32,300
Sitting next to Jin at a theater...

555
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:34,100
and watching a movie.

556
00:36:35,870 --> 00:36:39,840
My dream came true, but
I'm not happy at all.

557
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:45,210
It isn't because I am Hae Joo's fill-in.

558
00:36:46,250 --> 00:36:49,020
It's because Jin seems so sad,

559
00:36:49,520 --> 00:36:52,820
but there's nothing I
can do to comfort him.

560
00:36:58,890 --> 00:37:00,030
Father?

561
00:37:04,470 --> 00:37:05,500
What's wrong?

562
00:37:08,200 --> 00:37:10,070
Father? Watching a movie?

563
00:37:11,040 --> 00:37:12,240
That's odd.

564
00:37:15,710 --> 00:37:17,580
- My father.
- Father?

565
00:37:17,580 --> 00:37:19,810
- My father.
- Let's go.

566
00:37:31,660 --> 00:37:33,860
I'm sorry, Jin.

567
00:37:34,830 --> 00:37:35,860
It's okay.

568
00:37:36,330 --> 00:37:38,330
You'll get in trouble if
your father sees you.

569
00:37:41,700 --> 00:37:42,800
Let's go eat.

570
00:37:43,740 --> 00:37:45,110
How about dumplings?

571
00:37:46,170 --> 00:37:47,210
Sounds good.

572
00:37:52,450 --> 00:37:55,050
What? Auntie?

573
00:37:56,620 --> 00:37:57,620
Let's go.

574
00:37:59,790 --> 00:38:00,920
Okay.

575
00:38:05,330 --> 00:38:07,430
Maybe I was mistaken.

576
00:38:08,330 --> 00:38:10,330
2, 4.

577
00:38:13,770 --> 00:38:16,970
We're so busy. Why is it so busy today?

578
00:38:16,970 --> 00:38:19,970
I couldn't even pee today.

579
00:38:22,680 --> 00:38:23,710
Hey.

580
00:38:24,180 --> 00:38:27,150
Did Auntie say when she'd be back?

581
00:38:27,420 --> 00:38:29,620
She's delivering products
to Hyangcheon-dong Market,

582
00:38:29,750 --> 00:38:31,990
and visiting a relative who lives there.

583
00:38:32,120 --> 00:38:33,250
Okay.

584
00:38:34,360 --> 00:38:36,760
Auntie had a relative...

585
00:38:36,830 --> 00:38:38,560
in Hyangcheon-dong?

586
00:38:47,340 --> 00:38:48,900
We're friends, right?

587
00:38:49,070 --> 00:38:50,770
Yes, of course.

588
00:38:51,570 --> 00:38:54,480
I can't see you anymore.

589
00:38:54,710 --> 00:38:56,340
I came to tell you that.

590
00:38:57,050 --> 00:38:58,810
We have to break up now.

591
00:38:59,480 --> 00:39:00,850
I mean it.

592
00:39:01,050 --> 00:39:03,950
I don't think we are a suitable pair.

593
00:39:09,120 --> 00:39:11,760
Smile, Yang Ja. Keep your promise.

594
00:39:12,130 --> 00:39:13,160
Earlier...

595
00:39:26,110 --> 00:39:27,310
Why aren't you eating?

596
00:39:28,580 --> 00:39:29,910
Don't you like dumplings?

597
00:39:30,150 --> 00:39:32,280
Yes, I do.

598
00:39:32,580 --> 00:39:35,180
Eat up. This place is famous.

599
00:39:35,850 --> 00:39:36,850
Okay.

600
00:39:43,830 --> 00:39:44,960
It's strange.

601
00:39:45,390 --> 00:39:47,260
Why does it taste so bad?

602
00:39:48,230 --> 00:39:49,400
Jung Hee.

603
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:51,970
She ate so well when she came with me.

604
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:55,270
What? Is she acting coy in front of Jin?

605
00:39:58,710 --> 00:39:59,870
Dong Moon?

606
00:40:07,820 --> 00:40:08,950
Dong Moon again?

607
00:40:14,690 --> 00:40:15,690
That's right.

608
00:40:16,190 --> 00:40:17,290
Dong Moon.

609
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:19,660
You're always out playing.

610
00:40:19,690 --> 00:40:20,780
When do you study?

611
00:40:21,100 --> 00:40:23,060
I heard you came in first
in your grade again.

612
00:40:23,570 --> 00:40:24,870
First in his entire grade?

613
00:40:25,270 --> 00:40:26,400
For real?

614
00:40:26,900 --> 00:40:30,540
You're much smarter than you look.

615
00:40:31,070 --> 00:40:32,070
Well...

616
00:40:43,180 --> 00:40:44,220
You two eat.

617
00:40:44,820 --> 00:40:45,820
I'll go first.

618
00:40:47,520 --> 00:40:48,520
But...

619
00:40:49,090 --> 00:40:50,330
Bye.

620
00:40:52,090 --> 00:40:53,090
What...

621
00:40:58,170 --> 00:40:59,200
Jung Hee.

622
00:41:08,540 --> 00:41:09,540
What?

623
00:41:10,880 --> 00:41:13,310
I wanted to say bye.

624
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:17,190
Thank you for taking me...

625
00:41:17,890 --> 00:41:19,120
to the movie.

626
00:41:25,830 --> 00:41:27,660
- Jung Hee.
- Yes?

627
00:41:28,030 --> 00:41:29,130
I was sorry...

628
00:41:30,330 --> 00:41:31,770
for many things.

629
00:41:32,930 --> 00:41:34,370
You're a good kid.

630
00:41:35,840 --> 00:41:36,870
You're kind...

631
00:41:37,870 --> 00:41:38,970
and cute.

632
00:41:46,250 --> 00:41:47,250
Bye.

633
00:42:18,650 --> 00:42:20,320
You're leaving?

634
00:42:21,250 --> 00:42:24,050
Yes. I found a job near my parents' home.

635
00:42:25,750 --> 00:42:27,320
- Also...
- Also what?

636
00:42:28,860 --> 00:42:30,690
I can't do this...

637
00:42:34,430 --> 00:42:35,430
Do Ha.

638
00:42:36,430 --> 00:42:37,530
Must you go?

639
00:42:37,530 --> 00:42:38,770
I'm sorry.

640
00:42:43,940 --> 00:42:45,640
Aren't you Jung Hee's Auntie?

641
00:42:45,770 --> 00:42:46,780
Auntie...

642
00:42:51,410 --> 00:42:53,150
Jung Hee's father.

643
00:43:03,060 --> 00:43:04,560
Stop following me.

644
00:43:05,560 --> 00:43:07,030
I'm not following you.

645
00:43:07,060 --> 00:43:08,330
I'm walking you home.

646
00:43:08,860 --> 00:43:10,730
It's dangerous at night.

647
00:43:11,170 --> 00:43:12,370
Leave.

648
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:13,970
I'm home now.

649
00:43:14,470 --> 00:43:16,070
Was I that wrong?

650
00:43:20,380 --> 00:43:23,280
- What?
- Is it my fault that...

651
00:43:24,450 --> 00:43:26,080
I was there when you were on a date?

652
00:43:26,150 --> 00:43:27,550
It wasn't a date.

653
00:43:29,520 --> 00:43:30,650
At least you know.

654
00:43:33,420 --> 00:43:34,420
Hey.

655
00:43:35,390 --> 00:43:36,460
Don't you...

656
00:43:37,430 --> 00:43:39,060
follow me anymore.

657
00:43:39,360 --> 00:43:40,760
It's annoying.

658
00:43:44,700 --> 00:43:46,170
I'm annoying?

659
00:43:47,370 --> 00:43:48,400
I'm also...

660
00:43:49,770 --> 00:43:53,110
sick of following you like a puppy dog...

661
00:43:53,110 --> 00:43:54,310
when you don't even look at me.

662
00:43:56,440 --> 00:43:57,550
I'll stop.

663
00:43:58,780 --> 00:44:00,650
I won't follow you around anymore.

664
00:44:01,480 --> 00:44:02,480
Sorry...

665
00:44:03,490 --> 00:44:04,690
for annoying you.

666
00:44:22,240 --> 00:44:23,610
You brat.

667
00:44:23,970 --> 00:44:26,440
Where were you this late at night?

668
00:44:27,180 --> 00:44:29,680
Why is your skirt so short?

669
00:44:29,740 --> 00:44:31,280
Maybe I grew.

670
00:44:32,380 --> 00:44:33,850
I was at Eun Ja's house.

671
00:44:36,950 --> 00:44:38,190
Madam.

672
00:44:38,750 --> 00:44:40,020
I'm sorry I'm late.

673
00:44:40,020 --> 00:44:41,520
No need to be sorry.

674
00:44:41,520 --> 00:44:43,660
You need time off too.

675
00:44:44,190 --> 00:44:46,490
I should be doing that.

676
00:44:46,490 --> 00:44:48,000
I'll change and come out.

677
00:44:48,000 --> 00:44:49,000
Auntie.

678
00:44:50,170 --> 00:44:52,200
- What?
- Today, at Hyangcheon...

679
00:44:56,400 --> 00:44:57,410
Never mind.

680
00:44:58,870 --> 00:45:00,710
Mom, Father was...

681
00:45:06,380 --> 00:45:07,380
Never mind.

682
00:45:08,280 --> 00:45:10,650
Punk. What about your father?

683
00:45:10,650 --> 00:45:11,650
Nothing.

684
00:45:11,650 --> 00:45:13,820
What? What did he do?

685
00:45:16,420 --> 00:45:17,530
Go rest.

686
00:45:18,960 --> 00:45:19,960
Okay.

687
00:45:21,930 --> 00:45:23,030
I couldn't tell Mom...

688
00:45:23,230 --> 00:45:25,670
that I saw Father in the theater...

689
00:45:28,770 --> 00:45:31,710
or that I saw Auntie...

690
00:45:33,310 --> 00:45:35,440
in front of the theater.

691
00:45:39,380 --> 00:45:41,580
Because she can't know that I went...

692
00:45:41,580 --> 00:45:43,120
to that theater.

693
00:45:46,150 --> 00:45:48,120
No. It was more because...

694
00:45:50,290 --> 00:45:51,490
It was more because...

695
00:46:06,210 --> 00:46:08,240
My instincts told me...

696
00:46:08,710 --> 00:46:11,750
there was a bigger reason
why I shouldn't say...

697
00:46:12,480 --> 00:46:14,450
I was in Hyangcheon-dong.

698
00:46:19,520 --> 00:46:21,520
Dangerous instincts.

699
00:46:23,060 --> 00:46:24,160
Where are we going?

700
00:46:24,160 --> 00:46:26,730
I told you. I need to tell you something.

701
00:46:26,730 --> 00:46:28,600
- Let go.
- Come here.

702
00:46:28,600 --> 00:46:29,930
Stop it.

703
00:46:29,930 --> 00:46:32,030
Don't be like that. Just have one drink.

704
00:46:32,030 --> 00:46:34,470
Let go already.

705
00:46:35,240 --> 00:46:37,240
That brat.

706
00:46:37,610 --> 00:46:39,740
Get over here. Come on.

707
00:46:39,740 --> 00:46:41,310
Come here.

708
00:46:41,310 --> 00:46:43,710
- Just one drink.
- Stop it. Let go.

709
00:46:48,480 --> 00:46:50,290
Hey, Young Choon.

710
00:46:50,920 --> 00:46:52,720
Didn't you switch from Ae Sook...

711
00:46:53,220 --> 00:46:54,360
to the communist?

712
00:46:54,960 --> 00:46:57,330
- Communist?
- That's right. Communist.

713
00:46:58,060 --> 00:47:00,430
Communist?

714
00:47:00,430 --> 00:47:03,200
- Stop it. Young Choon.
- You want to die?

715
00:47:03,200 --> 00:47:05,100
Stop it already.

716
00:47:05,100 --> 00:47:08,300
What if you end up back in the slammer?

717
00:47:08,670 --> 00:47:10,270
Stop it.

718
00:47:17,880 --> 00:47:19,910
This is nice.

719
00:47:20,420 --> 00:47:22,680
The night air is sweet.

720
00:47:23,690 --> 00:47:26,320
- Let go.
- I don't want to.

721
00:47:26,990 --> 00:47:28,020
Do you want to walk?

722
00:47:35,330 --> 00:47:36,630
Young Choon.

723
00:47:38,700 --> 00:47:41,340
You like Hae Joo, don't you?

724
00:47:43,270 --> 00:47:45,270
There's a bad rumor about her.

725
00:47:45,640 --> 00:47:47,080
There's a bad rumor about you too.

726
00:47:48,580 --> 00:47:49,640
Same for me.

727
00:47:49,640 --> 00:47:52,580
I don't care about that.

728
00:47:54,080 --> 00:47:55,880
As long as you...

729
00:47:56,550 --> 00:47:58,220
like me...

730
00:48:02,620 --> 00:48:03,630
Walk home.

731
00:48:37,860 --> 00:48:39,060
Mister.

732
00:48:39,260 --> 00:48:40,530
Why are you out here?

733
00:48:41,760 --> 00:48:42,930
Is something wrong?

734
00:48:42,930 --> 00:48:45,470
Just. I wanted some air.

735
00:48:46,370 --> 00:48:47,870
I thought I'd take a walk.

736
00:48:54,140 --> 00:48:55,140
Okay, then.

737
00:48:58,210 --> 00:48:59,310
If you want some air,

738
00:49:01,380 --> 00:49:02,680
how about a ride?

739
00:49:29,940 --> 00:49:31,250
Hold on tight.

740
00:49:31,850 --> 00:49:32,880
You'll get hurt.

741
00:49:46,030 --> 00:49:47,100
Hold on tight.

742
00:49:47,760 --> 00:49:48,760
I'm going to speed up.

743
00:50:04,750 --> 00:50:06,110
I don't care either.

744
00:50:07,150 --> 00:50:08,480
As long as...

745
00:50:09,220 --> 00:50:11,320
I can look at you without anyone's knowing,

746
00:50:12,450 --> 00:50:13,620
it doesn't matter.

747
00:50:35,310 --> 00:50:38,410
I was sorry for many things.

748
00:50:41,850 --> 00:50:43,250
Jin.

749
00:50:44,420 --> 00:50:46,350
Is something wrong?

750
00:51:06,610 --> 00:51:09,840
What the... Why did Dong Moon show up?

751
00:51:10,980 --> 00:51:12,510
Get lost, Dong Moon.

752
00:51:32,830 --> 00:51:34,240
What the...

753
00:51:40,140 --> 00:51:41,510
Dong Moon...

754
00:51:42,410 --> 00:51:44,450
seemed really hurt.

755
00:51:52,390 --> 00:51:54,420
Hello, Mr. Bae.

756
00:51:54,560 --> 00:51:57,930
Thank you for coming even on a Sunday.

757
00:51:58,990 --> 00:52:01,500
But... Are you going out?

758
00:52:02,900 --> 00:52:06,130
I'm going to a gathering, sir.

759
00:52:06,470 --> 00:52:08,740
Please, there's no need to be so formal.

760
00:52:08,740 --> 00:52:09,840
Yes, there is.

761
00:52:10,070 --> 00:52:13,410
You work so hard to teach
our two birdbrains.

762
00:52:13,480 --> 00:52:15,980
I must be formal and respectful.

763
00:52:16,540 --> 00:52:17,780
Mom, are you going...

764
00:52:19,680 --> 00:52:22,120
You're not going like that, are you?

765
00:52:23,820 --> 00:52:25,420
Why? Is it weird?

766
00:52:25,590 --> 00:52:28,560
It's crazy weird. You'll make people sick.

767
00:52:30,290 --> 00:52:31,560
You punk.

768
00:52:33,290 --> 00:52:37,200
You punk. Listen to your teacher,

769
00:52:37,200 --> 00:52:39,200
and study hard. Got it?

770
00:52:39,730 --> 00:52:42,600
Jung Hee! Your teacher's here!

771
00:52:42,970 --> 00:52:44,040
Jung Hee!

772
00:52:46,810 --> 00:52:48,810
- I'm not deaf.
- Gibberish.

773
00:52:49,940 --> 00:52:51,210
I'll go now.

774
00:52:56,650 --> 00:52:58,190
Mom, you should...

775
00:52:58,920 --> 00:53:00,120
Gibberish.

776
00:53:03,790 --> 00:53:06,530
- Hello.
- Hello.

777
00:53:07,900 --> 00:53:10,830
- Jung Hee's dad?
- I saw with my own eyes.

778
00:53:11,700 --> 00:53:12,970
Gibberish.

779
00:53:13,270 --> 00:53:15,340
Why are we meeting here and wasting money?

780
00:53:15,340 --> 00:53:17,170
We could've just met in our neighborhood.

781
00:53:23,750 --> 00:53:25,150
Were you badmouthing me again?

782
00:53:25,380 --> 00:53:27,050
That I have a bad temper.

783
00:53:27,480 --> 00:53:29,020
Go ahead, keep going.

784
00:53:29,520 --> 00:53:32,950
It's not like you're cutting me open.

785
00:53:33,220 --> 00:53:36,490
It doesn't hurt me, so go right ahead.

786
00:53:38,960 --> 00:53:40,860
How could you say that?

787
00:54:06,720 --> 00:54:07,720
What?

788
00:54:11,790 --> 00:54:12,890
Didn't you tell her?

789
00:54:13,360 --> 00:54:15,730
About what? Oh, that?

790
00:54:15,760 --> 00:54:17,730
No, not yet.

791
00:54:18,970 --> 00:54:20,000
About what?

792
00:54:21,970 --> 00:54:24,610
- What is it?
- About... You know, Jin.

793
00:54:24,610 --> 00:54:26,980
Jin is transferring to a school in Seoul.

794
00:54:32,210 --> 00:54:34,420
He's leaving today, right?

795
00:54:35,450 --> 00:54:37,620
Since Jin's father...

796
00:54:37,750 --> 00:54:39,250
is loaded,

797
00:54:39,420 --> 00:54:41,860
he processed the transfer in like a day.

798
00:54:45,130 --> 00:54:47,600
When will we ever solve all of these?

799
00:54:54,800 --> 00:54:55,900
Jung Hee.

800
00:54:56,370 --> 00:54:58,510
I'm going to get my workbook.

801
00:55:03,880 --> 00:55:05,180
Okay, okay.

802
00:55:11,090 --> 00:55:12,190
He's leaving?

803
00:55:13,720 --> 00:55:15,090
He's leaving like this?

804
00:55:19,690 --> 00:55:20,860
Then, was that...

805
00:55:22,560 --> 00:55:24,170
the last time?

806
00:55:32,070 --> 00:55:33,640
Go if he wants. Whatever.

807
00:55:47,160 --> 00:55:48,320
Here.

808
00:55:49,290 --> 00:55:51,060
- Take this with you.
- What about you?

809
00:55:51,490 --> 00:55:52,630
I'm fine.

810
00:55:55,060 --> 00:55:56,630
This isn't right.

811
00:56:10,410 --> 00:56:11,510
You're brave.

812
00:56:12,110 --> 00:56:13,210
Are you hurt?

813
00:56:16,380 --> 00:56:17,720
You almost fell again.

814
00:56:18,550 --> 00:56:19,950
This isn't right.

815
00:56:21,320 --> 00:56:23,790
Even if I meant nothing...

816
00:56:24,090 --> 00:56:25,860
to Jin,

817
00:56:27,660 --> 00:56:29,060
this isn't right.

818
00:56:31,600 --> 00:56:32,870
Seoul, please.

819
00:56:53,290 --> 00:56:54,390
Jung Hee.

820
00:56:55,960 --> 00:56:57,060
Jung Hee!

821
00:57:08,440 --> 00:57:09,500
Get on.

822
00:57:11,010 --> 00:57:14,180
You can't see Jin if you run there.

823
00:57:15,540 --> 00:57:16,950
Get on. Hurry.

824
00:57:33,030 --> 00:57:34,730
(Bus Schedule)

825
00:58:06,960 --> 00:58:09,360
That's it. That's his bus.

826
00:58:19,170 --> 00:58:20,340
Jin!

827
00:58:20,540 --> 00:58:21,840
Jin!
